# Files that should NEVER be reformatted by Prettier.
#
# Background: Prettier's default markdown formatting normalises nested
# list-continuation indentation (4-space -> 2-space) and collapses some
# wrapped-bullet whitespace. The repo's tracking docs intentionally use
# the wider continuation style for readability, and our markdown house
# style is enforced manually + via .editorconfig, not by Prettier.
#
# Letting Prettier touch these files produces purely-cosmetic diffs that
# mask real edits and create merge friction. So we exclude them here.
# See .zed/settings.json for the editor-level safeguard.

# Tracking files (high churn, manual formatting):
TODO.md
PROGRESS.md
CHANGELOG.md
README.md

# All ADRs use manual formatting per ADR-032 conventions:
docs/adr/

# The v1 spec is hand-formatted:
docs/SPEC.md
docs/PLAN.md
docs/CONVENTIONS.md

# Frozen v0 archive — never touch:
docs/v0/

# Project-local agent guidance:
CLAUDE.md
AGENTS.md
